  'text_export_2' => 'Product filter',
  'text_export_2_1' => 'Products',
  'text_export_2_1_help' => '<b>Upload only</b> - unloads only selected products despite the settings of the category, brands, etc. <hr><b>Prohibit unload</b> - unloads all products, taking into account the settings except selected. They will not be included in the unloading.<hr><b>We also unload</b> - unloading of all goods taking into account the settings + selected ones, even if they do not go through the settings.',
  'text_export_2_1_mode1' => 'We export only',
  'text_export_2_1_mode2' => 'Disable exporting',
  'text_export_2_1_mode3' => 'We also export',
  'text_export_2_1_place' => 'Enter product name or article number',
  'text_export_2_1_list1' => 'Edit. Opens in a new tab',
  'text_export_2_1_list2' => 'View product. Opens in a new tab',
  'text_export_2_2' => 'Categories',
  'text_export_2_2_help' => 'Upload products only from the selected categories.<br>You should always select the final categories. Categories higher in the hierarchy will be in the feed in the categories block.<br>In some marketplaces, categories are not displayed - this is normal.<br>If there is a plus after a category, the category has subcategories and when you click on a category, its subcategories will open.<br>For select a category, click on the slider on the left',
  'text_select_all' => 'Select all',
  'text_unselect_all' => 'Remove all',
  'text_export_2_3' => 'Brands',
  'text_export_2_3_help' => 'Upload products of some brands.<br>To select a manufacturer, just click on it',
  'text_export_2_4' => 'Export logic',
  'text_export_2_4_help' => 'Hard binding - products of selected categories and only selected brands; Plus - products of selected categories as well as products of selected brands.<hr>For more accurate filtering, it is recommended to select mode 1 with the logic only products of selected brands and in selected categories.',
  'text_export_2_4_1' => 'Products of selected categories AND only selected brands',
  'text_export_2_4_2' => 'Products of selected categories AND products of selected brands',
  'text_export_2_5' => 'Link to main category',
  'text_export_2_5_help' => 'If you use SEOPRO there is a main category. If it is set as final and the main category is indicated in all products, then mark link.<hr>If SEOPRO is not used or the main category is not indicated in the products, it is better not to include it. Unloading will try to pick up the final product category if it is linked to many.',
  'text_export_2_5_1' => 'We are tied to the main category (the main category is indicated in all products and as the final one in the chain)',
  'text_export_2_5_2' => 'We are not tied to the main category. Let UniXML itself find the final product category',
  'text_export_2_5_none' => 'You do not have a CNC generation system - SEOPRO. But everything will work without SEO.<br>It is recommended to install it. This is useful for both UniXML and SEO in general.',
  'text_export_2_6' => 'Link to availability (quantity)',
  'text_export_2_6_help' => 'Unload all goods even with zero balance. By default, unloading picks up only goods in stock.<br>This is necessary for stores that are not linked to product balances or to update data when there is no product in the store',
  'text_export_2_6_1' => 'We don\'t get attached, we even export what is not in stock',
  'text_export_2_6_2' => 'We are getting attached, we only export in stock',
  'text_export_2_6_stat' => 'In stock status',
  'text_export_2_6_stat_help' => 'The status of the product in the Data tab at which the product will be in stock, even if its balance is 0',
  'text_export_2_7' => 'Link to photo',
  'text_export_2_7_help' => 'This is a setting that allows you not to upload products without a photo<hr>Upload products even without a photo - in this case, products even those that do not have a photo are included in the feed<hr>Do not upload products without a photo - this mode filters products and those that have photos are unloaded. This is important for most marketplaces',
  'text_export_2_7_1' => 'Upload products even without photos',
  'text_export_2_7_2' => 'DO NOT upload products without photos',
  'text_export_3' => 'Content changes',
  'text_export_3_1' => 'Markup/discount on goods',
  'text_export_3_1_help' => 'This is a setting that specifies a price adjustment, in other words, a markup or discount. You can record it in different ways. For example, +10% or 10% will work the same and will add +10% to the price of all products. If you write -10% then there will be a 10% discount<hr>You can also use multiplication or division. For example, by writing /2, the prices will be divided by 2. If you enter *1.45, this will multiply the price by the given number 1.45<hr>You can specify not only percentages or multiplication/division operators, but also add +100 to the prices by writing +100. And it also works with minus',
  'text_export_3_1_place' => '10% is 10% on the price or 200 is 200 units of currency',
  'text_export_3_2' => 'Multiply product by options',
  'text_export_3_2_help' => 'This item allows you to multiply one product into its variations, as required by marketplaces.<br>For example, you have a T-shirt, it has the options Color (Blue/Red) and Size (S/M/L). By selecting these options in the sets, we will get 6 different offers at the output<hr><b>Be sure to read the information on how to configure everything correctly</b>, to do this, just click where your mouse cursor is now',
  'text_export_3_2_add' => 'Add options to set',
  'text_export_in' => 'in',
  'text_export_in_pro' => 'products',
  'text_export_3_2_values' => 'Values:',
  'text_export_3_2_add_text' => 'Add dialing options',
  'text_export_3_2_optionset' => 'Option set',
  'text_export_3_2_optionset_delete' => 'Delete set',
  'text_export_3_2_option_in_feed' => 'The upload will include:',
  'text_export_3_2_add_a_set_of_options' => 'Add a set of options',
  'text_export_3_2_none_options' => 'There are no options in the store yet.<br>As there will be options - there will be a setting for which options to multiply the product.',
  'text_export_3_3' => 'Template for generating product names',
  'text_export_3_3_help' => 'In some cases, a special name for a product of a certain structure is required. Using the template, you can generate the product name on the fly.<hr><b>((table.field))</b> - field from the database. The table can be p - product and pd - product_description. Example: ((p.quantity)) or ((pd.meta_title))<br><b>{{attribute}}</b> - attribute name (if not found, not displayed),<br><b> [[optionset3]]</b> - name of the option (works in case of multiplying a product by an option). You can look at paragraph 3.2<br><b>{array field}</b> - any field of an array of products, for example name (already generated), manufacturer, special, etc.<br>',
  'text_export_db_fields' => 'What fields are available?',
  'text_export_3_4' => 'Template for generating product descriptions',
  'text_export_3_4_help' => 'In some cases, a special description of a product of a certain structure is required. Using the template, you can generate product descriptions on the fly.<hr><b>((table.field))</b> - field from the database. The table can be p - product and pd - product_description. Example: ((p.quantity)) or ((pd.meta_title))<br><b>{{attribute}}</b> - attribute name (if not found, not displayed),<br><b> [[optionset3]]</b> - name of the option (works in case of multiplying a product by an option). You can look at paragraph 3.2<br><b>{array field}</b> - any field of an array of products, for example name (already generated), manufacturer, special, etc.<br>',
  'text_export_3_5' => 'Generation mode',
  'text_export_3_5_help' => 'This is a setting that allows you to specify when to generate a description<hr>Generate a description even if it exists (forced according to the template above) - With this choice, the description is generated even when the description itself is in the product.<br>Generate a description only if it is not there, if we select this option, the description is generated only if the product does not have a description.<hr>Often marketplaces need descriptions but they are not in the store, then this item is suitable for creating a stub.',
  'text_export_3_5_1' => 'Generate a description even if it exists (forced according to the template above)',
  'text_export_3_5_2' => 'Generate a description only if there is none',
  'text_export_3_6' => 'Descriptions clearing mode',
  'text_export_3_6_help' => 'This is a setting that allows you to choose how to clear the description and whether to clear it at all. There are 3 operating modes of the setting<hr><b>Clear the description from special characters and html tags (if you just need text)</b> - in this mode, any description with any tags or formatting will appear in the feed as just text.<br> <b>Clean the description only from styles and unnecessary tags. We leave the basic tags (recommended)</b> - in this mode, the output we get is a clean formatted html description code without anything extra.<br><b>DO NOT clean the description - upload the original (1 in 1 as on the site)</b > - with this setting, the description in the feed will be 1 to 1 as in the database.',
  'text_export_3_6_1' => 'Clear the description from special characters and html tags (if you just need text)',
  'text_export_3_6_2' => 'Clean the description only from styles and unnecessary tags. We leave the basic tags (recommended)',
  'text_export_3_6_3' => 'DO NOT clear the description - upload the original (1in1 as on the website)',
  'text_export_3_7' => 'Category matching, category markup and custom category tags',
  'text_export_3_7_help' => 'Other category names can be uploaded. This is necessary so that there is an exact match with the categories of the marketplace. To select a category, <b>be sure to click</b> on it from the drop-down list!<br>Markup allows you to add a markup to products of a certain category.<br>Custom tags allow you to display your own information for products of a certain category<hr><b> We write tags and their values in the format (each tag and value on a new line, delimiter ==)</b><br>What can be used in custom tags:<br><b>((table.field))</b > - field from the database. The table can be p - product and pd - product_description. Example: ((p.quantity)) or ((pd.meta_title))<br><b>{{attribute}}</b> - attribute name (if not found, not displayed),<br><b> [[optionset3]]</b> - name of the option (works in case of multiplying a product by an option). You can look at paragraph 3.2<br><b>{array field}</b> - any field of an array of products, for example name (already generated), manufacturer, special, etc.<br>',
  'text_export_3_7_table_header' => '<thead><tr><td class="text-left">Store category</td><td class="text-left">Category in upload</td><td class=" text-left">Markup</td><td class="text-left">Tags and their meanings</td><td></td></tr></thead>',
  'text_export_3_7_cat_name' => 'Enter something from the category name',
  'text_export_3_7_xml_name' => 'The name of this category in the upload',
  'text_export_3_7_markup' => 'Markup on category products',
  'text_export_3_7_tag' => 'Tags for products in this category',
  'text_export_3_8' => 'Attribute export',
  'text_export_3_8_help' => 'Some marketplaces do not require characteristics. Therefore, this is the very case, it is better to turn them off so as not to load the database',
  'text_export_3_8_1' => 'Export attributes',
  'text_export_3_8_2' => 'Do not export attributes',
  'text_export_3_8_replace' => 'Attribute matching',
  'text_export_3_8_replace_help' => '<b>Store attribute</b> - here you need to start entering the name and a list of found attributes will appear below. To select - <b>be sure to click</b> on the desired one so that the attribute id is transferred to the system.<br><b>Attribute in upload</b> - here you can simply enter the name as it should be in the feed. As a rule, they write a name such as this property is called on the marketplace.<hr>Please note that if we set matches, then what is specified will be displayed in the feed. This way we can explicitly specify which attributes to unload and immediately rename them.',
  'text_export_3_8_replace_attr_oc' => 'Store attribute',
  'text_export_3_8_replace_attr_xml' => 'Attribute in export',
  'text_export_3_9' => 'Markups for product groups',
  'text_export_3_9_help' => 'This settings item allows you to make markups on goods individually or on a group of goods. For example, we need to make a markup on certain 10 products +40%<hr><b>Group name</b> This is just a name within the system, purely to designate a group of products.<br><b>Products</b> There is a field here input to search for a product (standard autocomplete) Enter the first characters of the name, article or id of the product and click from the drop-down list.<br><b>Markup</b> Here you can enter a markup/discount, everything is as in paragraph 3.1. For example -10% or +100.<hr>When adding products here, other discounts (general and per category) will not work!',
  'text_export_3_9_markup_table_header' => '<thead><tr><td class="text-left">Group</td><td class="text-left">Products</td><td class="text-left" ">Markup</td><td></td></tr></thead>',
  'text_name' => 'Title',
  'text_export_3_9_pro_import' => 'Import goods',
  'text_export_3_9_pro_import2' => 'Import',
  'text_export_3_9_pro_entry_name' => 'Enter product name, article or id',
  'text_export_3_9_pro_markup' => 'Markup',
  'text_export_3_9_table_help' => 'When adding products here, other discounts (general and per category) will not work.<br>The markup can be either "10%" or a fixed number, for example "100"',
  'text_export_3_10' => 'Word replacements',
  'text_export_3_10_help' => 'This settings item allows you to create lists of data replacements in the feed<hr><b>What we change</b> Here we write the word or string that needs to be replaced.<br><b>What we change it to</b> Here we write the word or string that needs to be replaced. If you need to cut it out, don’t write anything here, leave it blank.<br><b>Where to change</b> Here you can choose where to make replacements. Through this item, you can essentially compare attribute values. If you need to change something in a category then there is point 3.7<br>',
  'text_export_3_10_from' => 'What are we changing',
  'text_export_3_10_to' => 'What are we exchanging for',
  'text_export_3_10_where' => 'Where change',
  'text_export_3_10_name' => 'In the title',
  'text_export_3_10_model' => 'In model',
  'text_export_3_10_man' => 'In the manufacturer',
  'text_export_3_10_desc' => 'In the description',
  'text_export_3_10_url' => 'In the link',
  'text_export_3_10_image' => 'In photo',
  'text_export_3_10_attr_name' => 'In the name of the attributes',
  'text_export_3_10_attr_val' => 'In attribute values',
  'text_export_3_11' => 'Additional product photos',
  'text_export_3_11_help' => 'Some marketplaces accept additional product photos. It is recommended to include additional photos. However, where it is not necessary, turn it off so as not to overload the server once again',
  'text_export_3_11_1' => 'Upload additional photos',
  'text_export_3_11_2' => 'Do not upload additional photos',
  'text_export_3_12' => 'Additional static parameters',
  'text_export_3_12_help' => 'At this point you can add additional parameters or tags with any data<hr><b>Attribute name</b> Here you can write either just a name or a full tag. For example, if you need to display in the feed for each product the quantity &lt;quantity&gt;35&lt;/quantity&gt; in the Attribute name field we write &lt;quantity&gt;.<br>If you need to add a parameter to the feed &lt;param name="quantity"&gt;35&lt;/param&gt; In this field we simply write quantity. That is, what is in &lt;brackets&gt; then it will be displayed as a full-fledged tag.<br><b>Attribute text</b> This can be entered as static text Or use any variable, for example the {{Main voltage}} attribute or a field from the database ((p.viewed)) or a set of options [[optionset3]] or an array field {category}<hr>If additional parameters are specified here, they will be displayed in each product feed.',
  'text_export_3_12_name' => 'Name or tag',
  'text_export_3_12_text' => 'Value',
  'text_export_3_12_table_help' => 'As an attribute Text, you can specify not only static text but also variables:<br>{{attribute}} ((table.field)) [[optionset]] {array field}',
  'text_export_3_13' => 'Prefix to the product link (UTM, etc.)',
  'text_export_3_13_help' => 'This setting allows you to add additional parameters to the link. Often this is utm, but any can be used. You can also embed any substitutions and variables into the link prefix, as in other places in UniXML.<hr>For example, the prefix could be like this: ?utm=test&pid={product_id}&piddb=((p.product_id))&sostattr={{State }}&optset4=[[optionset4]]&optset3=[[optionset3]] where the ability to add any product data is demonstrated.',
  'text_export_4' => 'Custom code',
  'text_export_4_1' => 'Add request',
  'text_export_4_1_help' => 'Here you can send a request to the database. In the module, the query in a simplified form is as follows: SELECT the required fields FROM the required tables WHERE conditions AND p.upc != 1 and then query the module. Where And p.upc != 1 is what will be inserted from this field. Here you can add additional conditions for unloading.',
  'text_export_4_1_addon1' => 'SELECT fields FROM table WHERE conditions',
  'text_export_4_1_place' => 'And p.upc != 1 And p.custom_field = \'value\' -additional selection conditions',
  'text_export_4_1_addon2' => 'End of request',
  'text_export_4_2' => 'Custom code AFTER THE REQUEST in the database, BEFORE CROSSING in the loop',
  'text_export_4_2_help' => 'php syntax! We process the $query->rows array - if there is any selection of products with databases in one go<hr>Here it is convenient to place the code for selecting something to process the processing in the product cycle',
  'text_export_4_2_textarea' => 'Working with the $rows array. For example, foreach ($rows as $key => $product) { etc. The $data array is available - there are settings, you can see, for example, by running echo \'<pre>\';print_r($data);exit();',
  'text_export_4_3' => 'Custom code in the product iteration cycle',
  'text_export_4_3_help' => 'php syntax! We work with the $product array - this is an array with COLOR data<hr>Here it is convenient to place processing code for editing data in COLOR details',
  'text_export_4_3_place' => 'if($product[\'price\'] < 1000){$product[\'price\'] *= 1.1;}else{$product[\'price\'] *= 1.05; }',
  'text_export_4_4' => 'Custom code after loop traversal',
  'text_export_4_4_help' => 'php syntax! We work with a ready-made array of already processed product data $products<hr>Here is a ready-made array for generating XML',
  'text_export_4_4_place' => 'Here is a ready array',
  'text_export_5' => 'System settings',
  'text_export_5_1' => 'Additional fields with a base for export',
  'text_export_5_1_help' => 'Some are installed, you need to fetch additional data from the database. Since UniXML is a module with conservative code, nothing extra from the base is required. To take anything else, they need to be registered in this project. Comma delimiter<hr>Please note that if you have specified a selection of additional fields here, this means that they will only be taken with the database, wherever they are, they will not. If you need to put data in the additional static parameters item.',
  'text_export_5_2' => 'From which field is the product id pregnant',
  'text_export_5_2_help' => 'Many marketplaces have a connecting link - an identifier. You can specify what will be the identifier in this setting. Attention! The ID must only be a unique value. If the product is multiplied by options, there will be an option prefix to maintain the uniqueness of the identifier',
  'text_export_5_3' => 'From which field is the price',
  'text_export_5_3_help' => 'In many stores, the price for unloading is in a different field. So that the price comes from the desired field, just indicate it',
  'text_export_5_4' => 'Quantity at a time',
  'text_export_5_4_help' => 'The greater the number of products at a time, the faster the xml will be generated, but more RAM is required. The lower the number, the less RAM will be required, but the upload will take longer to generate. It is recommended about 10,000 products at a time, but if there are errors about insufficient RAM, reduce until the error disappears',
  'text_export_5_5' => 'Log upload',
  'text_export_5_5_help' => 'To understand whether everything is ok, whether everything is working and how quickly, you can enter the name of the log file where information about downloads will be recorded',
  'text_export_5_5_place' => 'For example: unixml.log can also be log_name.secret_ext - for protection. If empty, it is not logged',
  'text_export_5_6' => 'Startup protection key',
  'text_export_5_6_help' => 'The protection key allows you to set your parameter in the link for xml generation. This is necessary so that the link does not constantly launch generation that loads the site. By entering the key, the upload will be to the address with the prefix &key=secret_key',
  'text_export_5_6_small' => 'to follow the link, first save the settings for the protection to work',
  'text_export_5_7' => 'XML file name',
  'text_export_5_7_help' => 'Using this settings item, you can specify the name of the file to be generated. This is convenient because you can call it your own, for example rozetka34Hkfd.xml, and it will be unique. This is a kind of protection against accidentally receiving a file.<hr>A couple of examples:<br>If you enter <b>123</b> then the feed file will be at the link site.com/price/123.xml<br>If you enter < b>rozetka</b> and this file is already on the server, it will be at site.com/price/rozetka.xml and will replace the old one<br>If you register <b>123/435/rozetka_34243</b> then the feed will be at site.com/price/123/435/rozetka_34243.xml, that is, it will create subfolders',
  'text_export_5_8' => 'Product stores',
  'text_export_5_8_help' => 'You can only upload products for certain stores.',
  'text_export_6' => 'Information',
  'text_export_6_1' => 'Direct generation launch link',
  'text_export_6_1_file' => 'Link to start generation to file',
  'text_export_6_1_file_help' => 'Using this link, an export file is generated and when the process is completed, statistics of the module\'s operation in generation mode are displayed.',
  'text_export_6_1_help' => 'Using this link, UniXML generates a feed on the fly and sends it in a stream. For example, if you open this link through a browser, you will see the XML feed that will just be generated.',
  'text_copy' => 'Copy',
  'text_goto' => 'Goto',
  'text_export_6_1_1_title' => 'Don\'t forget to save your settings before launching! Opens in a new window.',
  'text_export_6_1_1_small' => 'Link to start generation in the stream. By clicking on it, the feed is generated directly in the browser.',
  'text_export_6_1_2_small' => 'Link to start generating to a file. By clicking on it, the feed is generated into a ready-made XML file. Upon completion, operation statistics are displayed.',
  'text_export_6_1_cron_title' => 'Command for CRON generation',
  'text_export_6_1_cron_title_help' => 'Here is an example of a command to run on the server via CRON. The team may be different on different hosting sites',
  'text_export_6_1_cron_title_help2' => '<small>CRON command for generating to a file. Having configured the launch on the server, the feed is generated into a ready-made XML file. <b>It may differ on different hostings!</b><br>For example, there may be something like wget -q -O /dev/null “generation link” - it’s better to check with your hosting support for the exact command for CRON</small>' ,
  'text_export_6_1_xml_file' => 'XML file',
  'text_export_6_1_xml_file_help' => 'Here is a link to the finished XML file that is generated by the command above.',
  'text_export_6_2' => 'Setup information',

  'text_export_6_2_desc' => '<h4>General and recommendations for settings</h4>
   <ul>
     <li><b style="display:block;padding:6px 10px;background:#F7FDFF;border:1px dashed #39b3d7;">View information on the official website <a href="https://unixml.pro/info /feed/{{feed}}" target="_blank">https://unixml.pro/info/feed/{{feed}}</a>.
         If the main page of the site https://unixml.pro opens, this means that there is no information or need for this information yet for {{feed}}.
         Look a little later or write to the author with any questions.</b></li>
     <li>Always make sure that the file or feed link is opened correctly in your browser. If there are a lot of products, the browser may slow down or freeze - then look in any other XML validator</li>
     <li>If your feed is not generated or you see an Allowed memory size error, this means that you are hitting the RAM limit on the server. It is recommended to reduce the number of products at a time in paragraph <a data-id="5-4" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">5.4</a>. For more details, see the tooltip to the settings item</li>
     <li>Check generation time and server load during generation. If it takes a long time, say more than 5-10 seconds, it is recommended to set the generation to a CRON task and send the ready-made feed to the marketplace(s). This way we will not load the server. Some marketplaces request your feed every hour and it\'s not a good idea to generate one every time. If everything is fast and there are no more than a couple thousand products, you can also give a direct link from item <a data-id="6-1" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">6.1 </a> "Link to start direct generation"</li>
     <li>For security, it is recommended to set the Startup Protection Key in item <a data-id="5-6" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">5.6</a> a also set an unreadable XML file name in the <a data-id="5-7" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">5.7</a> item, for example 34hmdf7. This way, only you will know the launch link and no one will accidentally find it, just like the finished file.</li>
     <li>When you have questions about setup, before contacting support, please <b>look at the information on the official website</b> <a href="https://unixml.pro/set/export/" target=" _blank" title="Opens in a new window" data-toggle="tooltip">https://unixml.pro/set/export/</a>. If you didn’t find anything, write to the author using contact details <a href="https://unixml.pro/support/" target="_blank" title="Opens in a new window" data-toggle="tooltip">https:/ /unixml.pro/support/</a></li>
   </ul>
   <h4>If <b>not all products are unloaded</b> it is recommended to check the following settings items</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><a data-id="2-1" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.1</a> - see if those products have been added to the list, or on the contrary, only some have been entered, and the rest (not in the list) will not be uploaded - this is under the condition “Upload only”</li>
          <li><a data-id="2-2" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.2</a> - check whether product categories are selected. You need to choose the final categories. And if there is a link to the main one, then select those categories that are designated as the main ones in the desired products</li>
          <li><a data-id="2-3" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.3</a> - check whether the required manufacturers are selected, if there is no binding - no need to choose anything</li>
          <li><a data-id="2-4" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.4</a> - if you have extra products, look at the unloading logic . If this item says “And also products”, then there will be a selection of categories as well as brands whose products may be from other categories</li>
          <li><a data-id="2-5" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.5</a> - if you set the link to the main category then in those For products that should go into the feed, the main category must be selected. If you do not set the link to the main one, UniXML will try to find it itself.</li>
          <li><a data-id="2-6" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.6</a> - check the balances of those products that are not in the upload, they must be greater than 0 if you chose to link to availability</li>
          <li><a data-id="2-7" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.7</a> - if you should be attached to a photo, check if there is a photo in goods</li>
          <li><a data-id="5-2" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">5.2</a> - check if there is a product id from another field, It is important that the field is unique. The offer ids must be unique in the feed, and if you have duplicates somewhere, then only one of the duplicates will be in the feed. For example, if you choose to take the product id from the p.upc field, then you need to be sure that the upc field contains unique values for all products</li>
          <li><b>Also check</b> in the “non-uploadable” products whether they have all the data. For example, if a product does not have a category specified, it will not be uploaded. If the product does not have a brand, but you have supplied the brands themselves, the product will not be unloaded. If you don’t need filtering by manufacturer, then in item <a data-id="2-3" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.3</a> you don’t need to select anything. Also, if you don’t need filtering by category in item <a data-id="2-2" class="gotoset" title="Go to settings" data-toggle="tooltip">2.2</a> we don’t set anything, however Please remember that products without specified categories (in the product itself) will not be unloaded. There must be a category in the product in any case.</li>
        </ul>',
  'text_export_fast_nav' => 'Fast navigation',
  'text_export_what_link' => '<a href="https://unixml.pro/info/feed/{{feed}}" class="btn btn-warning howset" target="_blank" title="Opens in a new window . If the main page of the site https://unixml.pro opens, this means that there is no information or need for this information for {{feed}}. Look a little later or write to the author with all questions" data-toggle="tooltip" data- placement="left">How to set up {{feed}}?</a>',
